ria<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Alfred_Hershey\" title=\"Alfred Hershey\">Alfred Hershey<\/a>, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Phage_Group\" title=\"Phage Group\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Phage Group<\/a> made substantial headway unraveling important aspects of <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cell_physiology\" title=\"Cell physiology\">cell physiology<\/a>. The three shared the 1969 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine\">Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine<\/a> \"for their discoveries concerning the replication mechanism and the genetic structure of viruses\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Max_Delbr%C3%BCck#cite_note-Nobel-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>He was the first physicist to predict what is now called <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Delbr%C3%BCck_scattering\" title=\"Delbr\u00fcck scattering\">Delbr\u00fcck scattering<\/a>.<\/p>","name":"Max Delbr\u00fcck","place_of_birth":"Berlin ,  German Empire","place_of_death":"Pasadena, California ,  United States","text":"Max Delbr\u00fcck ,  born in Germany , Physiology or Medicine, 1969","year":1969.0}